    "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@pid_eins\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>pid_eins</span></a></span> the point is. This hook stuff allows me to replace nscd with my own service  that is responsible for loading all the NSS modules and exposes that as varlink to resolved and userdbd.</p><p>That way I can make the NSS modules in question completely hidden outside of the daemon and guarantee they don't get dlopen() into random programs for which I'm not sure they are ABI compatible with the NSS modules in question.</p>",
